Improved Samba Mahsuri (RP Bio-226) is a high yielding fine grain rice variety released by Directorate of Rice Research (DRR), Hyderabad, India. The variety was developed using Marker assisted selection and has three major bacterial blight resistance genes Xa21, xa13 and xa5. All India Coordinated Rice Improved Project (AICRIP) conducted trails in multiple locations across India, and found positive results for resistance to bacterial blight.
